  "prompt": "Why was the part B in 70 marks theory of physical education removed by CBSE for the batch 2014-2015 class 12th?",
  "response": "The removal of Part B in the 70-mark theory exam for Physical Education by CBSE (Central Board of Secondary Education) for the batch 2014-2015 was part of a broader curriculum restructuring aimed at streamlining the assessment process and reducing the workload on students. The decision was likely influenced by several factors, including the need for a better balance between theoretical knowledge and practical skills, as well as feedback from educators regarding the effectiveness of the assessment format.\n\nSpecific reasons for such changes often include a focus on enhancing the quality of education, ensuring that the examination system reflects current educational priorities, and meeting the evolving needs of students. However, for more detailed information and insights on the specific decisions made during that period, it may be beneficial to refer to official CBSE announcements or educational circulars that were issued around that time.",
